Phase 3: Deploy to DEV
 
Step 3.1 — Test Locally First (Optional but Recommended)
Before pushing to dev, validate your code runs in a dev VM environment:
1. git clone your repo to a Brain/OPUS VM
2. cd into the repo and checkout your dev branch
3. In dev_env.sh, add your credentials on line 129:
--extra-index-url https://username:password@artifactory.fg.rbc.com/artifactory/api/pypi/pypi-cdn0/simple
4. Run: source dev_env.sh  (you should see 'Deployment Completed!')
5. Test run: ./spark_submit.sh all 20220601
⚠️ Note: If testing on OPUS, change DEPLOY_MODE_PYTHON=cluster to =client in spark_submit.sh before running.
 
Step 3.2 — Push to Dev Branch
• Create a dev branch: e.g., dev/credit-card-alerts-initial
• Commit all your changes (main.py, DAG file, spark_submit.sh, config yamls, src files)
• Push to GitHub: git push origin dev/credit-card-alerts-initial
• GitHub Actions (ci.yml) auto-triggers on push to any dev branch
• Helios automatically deploys to the Dev environment
 
Step 3.3 — Verify in Airflow DEV
• Access Airflow DEV at: The URL corresponding to your dev server in helios-config.yml
• Navigate to the DAGs list and search for your dag_id
• Trigger the DAG manually to test
• Check task logs for any errors
⚠️ Note: You must be added to AD Group: APP_CDN0_PROD_AIRFLOW_RW to access Airflow.
 
Phase 4: Deploy to Pre-Prod (Prod-Pilot / Staging)
Pre-Prod uses the staging branch. Direct pushes to staging are NOT allowed. You must raise a Pull Request from your dev branch.
 
