Important: Data Quality Check (Mandatory)
Using pydeequ to check your data quality before writing to output is a mandatory requirement per the framework guidelines.
Add to your ETL processing file:
from src.utils import dq
df_final.cache()
dq.checkDataQuality(spark_session, df_final)   # Line in your ETL file
df_final.unpersist()
Then customize the checks in src/utils/dq.py to match your dataset's requirements (nulls, row counts, data types, etc.).
⚠️ Note: If you don't have a data quality rule that applies, you must document the reason and notify your team lead.
 
